---
title: Toggle Switch
---

p.c-text
  | In order to use a toggle switch just use an <code>input type="checkbox"</code> with the classes <code>c-input</code>
  | and <code>c-input--toggle</code>. Also, in order to have the switch properly styled you must add an empty label for
  | the checkbox immediately after it's declaration.

.c-mb4.c-mt2
  div(style="display:flex; align-items: center")
    input(type="checkbox", class="c-input c-input--toggle", id="checkbox01")
    label(class="c-mr1", for="checkbox01")
    span Very important flag

  :code(lang="html")
    <input type="checkbox" class="c-input c-input--toggle" id="checkbox">
    <label for="checkbox"></label>
    <span>Very important flag</span>

p.c-text
  | The toggle switches by default contains the text <code>ON/OFF</code>, but we could disable it with the use of the
  | modifier <code>c-input--no-text</code>.

.c-mb4.c-mt2
  div(style="display:flex; align-items: center")
    input(type="checkbox", class="c-input c-input--toggle c-input--no-text", id="checkbox02")
    label(class="c-mr1", for="checkbox02")
    span Very important flag

  :code(lang="html")
    <input type="checkbox" class="c-input c-input--toggle c-input--no-text" id="checkbox">
    <label for="checkbox"></label>
    <span>Very important flag</span>
